metadata.name: untitled unmastered.
metadata.description:
A natural collaboration between the very talented multidisciplinary artist, Anubis, and I.

Anubis' visual beautifully encompasses the poem, in which I wrote about the beauty of alignment through the scope of a fleeting sunset.

"The sun was mango marmalade
And the sky went princess Peach,
Reflections on my skin hit a citrus tangerine,
Forsaking me a sweetness I'd only known heaven to forge, 
The secret of Venus uncovered once more

Of Atoms and apples
And Eve-nings never alike,
I bask in the fleetness of scenic alignment."
